snippet.textDisplay:
It all makes sense. But there are questions. Where is David's father? Also, will Hall Of The Machine King be the next game? I remember a certain title that slipped off the scene quite fast... Dead FM AKA Gate 2, not DOOR but GATE.

Maybe here we can learn what happened to David's father, there must be more to the story, It feels like we've got a Chekhov's gun here and David's dad has something to do with all of this. Nine will definitely have a bigger part to play than mentioned and I think that we'll find out what that is in the next gate, Dead FM.

I've noticed on the back of the cereal box that it doesn't mention games but rather gates, since this refers to the cartridges, these are basically the game's way of saying "games", this series is referring to a lot of gates and not games, all of these are accessible gates through which you can go to play games, like Hover Junkers. Gate 2 has to have something... Dead FM will be the next link. Duck Season could function as a Gate through which the other Gates can be accessed. Gate 1: Boneworks, Gate 2: Dead FM and then Gate 3: the Hall of the Machine King and maybe even something else, this universe is made up of layers, we might get more games or gates to access through our "Gammons".

This part will be a bit more Meta, so stop reading if you don't like that. These will be theories.

Mini Theory:

This game can easily do something different, we might already be in the Hall of the Machine King, I mean Monogon is this giant tech company and it obviously makes a ton of money, they are the king of the virtual system, they could already be the Machine King. Even Monogon's rival is named KINGBIT, they could be the machine king, both of these companies are big tech companies, they are both basically machine kings.

Big Theory

Monogon/ Stress Level 0 has incredible capabilities and even more immense "Meta" capabilities since Monogon is tapped into the void. Finding out that Stress Level 0 is a canon company that operates with/under Monogon means that this game, or rather "gate" company can tap into the void the same way Monogon and can therefore bring an even deeper layer to the already existing games.

We saw this with Duck Season PC, Boneworks PC or just an update could also throw us for a loop and unravel yet another layer of this universe. In the first GT Live episode, MatPat found a door that he couldn't open, he could clip through it, so maybe later in an update or reveal these locations can be accessed and we can learn more about, Monogon, Gammon and the entire bloody universe that this gate holds.

Conclusion:

This sounds like a crazy rant, but look at what's been revealed before, we found a dome with fantasy land being made, we were able to clip through David's house to find the bathroom and the secret rooms, we found a smaller scale of David's house, heck we even saw ourselves having an ODE or Dream in the previous game this is not far fetched at all if anything this is what Stress Level 0 has been teaching us throughout the entire series, dig deeper, we found a shovel in the tutorial area, why?

This game is like a pit, and just like you go lower and lower into the boneworks and the void, you can go deeper and deeper into this universe.

snippet.textDisplay: We follow the story of a pretty average family. We watched the daily routines of the kids during their childhood. One day a while the family was coming back home after an errand the neighbor suddenly loses control of the car and crashes it. He and his kids are fine but the wife gains life-threatening injuries which eventually resulted in her death (the grave in the backyard). The neighbor becomes very depressed over the loss of his wife and the son becomes very aggressive. One day the older son teases the sister by taking her doll and placing it on a wooden bridge on their house. The daughter goes to retrieve the doll but falls to her death instead. Now with the death of a child under the neighbors' supervision. The son is taken away and raised either at an orphanage or adopted. Later the son comes back to his home town and buys a house adjacent to his old house. He later realizes his dad is still their but wonders what his father is hiding. He eventually gets into the basement to find a ritual circle with indications to a mother and a daughter. It becomes clear that he's making a deal with the devil to try and get his lost wife and daughter. When he catches you he barries you alive and gain attempts to get his mother and daughter back. This is my theory, maybe become a video one day. Who knows.
